Starting November 23rd, 2016 testing will begin on the I-680 Express Lane toll signs, which will last until project completion in Spring 2017. During this time, motorists can expect to see a variety of test messages on the signs including &quot;TEST&quot;, &quot;TESTING&quot;, and &quot;TESTING IN PROGRESS&quot;, as well as system generated tolls, such as $0.00.&lt;p&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;In addition, there will be nightly lane closures on the northbound and southbound directions of I-680 between Walnut Creek and Dublin, in the lanes closest to the median. Approved construction work hours are: Monday through Thursday from 8 p.m. – 5 a.m., Friday from 8 p.m. – 7 a.m., Saturday from 7 p.m. to 10 a.m. &lt;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more project details, &lt;a href=&quot;http://bayareaexpresslanes.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/2016_Nov21_Construction-Update_Final.pdf&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;click here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;.
